rComments: classwasa waste of time, he talked too fast and went in 50 different directions at once.  He was always concerned about the time and just rambled words out. The marking by the TA was pretty useless, they did not offer  feedback, just a mark on the last page.

I thought he was a great prof. His lectures were always interesting and he tried to make them humorous as well. As long as you attended his lectures and read the material, you would do well in his class. His tests were sooo easy!

Really nice guy but he tended to get off topic a lot but the readings were interesting and always relevant. Students were successful if they kept on top of the readings and attended lectures. There was an issue regarding the marking of final paper which was not handled that well by Prof. Ahn and the TA, but other than that, a good class.
